        <div2>
          <head>
            <title type="main">
              <hi rend="b">New Music for <hi rend="i">Four Zoas</hi></hi>
            </title>
          </head>
          <p>The first concert performance of Robert Starer’s “Images of Man” was presented by the
Department of Music, Brooklyn College School of Performing Arts, on 15 December 1974 at Whitman Hall. The text
for “Images of Man” was freely selected from sections of <hi rend="i">The Four Zoas.</hi> The work is scored
for four soloists, four instruments (flute, horn, cello, and harp), four percussionists, and chorus. “Images
of Man” was commissioned by CBS Television for presentation at the National Cathedral in Washington, D. C., on
4 November 1973 and is scheduled for publication in the spring of 1975.</p>
        </div2>
      </div1>
